description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a vacancy for a Senior Assistant Technical Officer (SATO) to join our dedicated clinical trials dispensing team and assist with our increasing workload in the pharmacy clinical trials unit at the Bristol Royal Infirmary. The successful candidate will have an aptitude for practical work, good organisational skills, be able to follow written procedures and be able to communicate effectively. You must have completed your NVQ level 2 in Pharmacy Services (or be nearing completion). Duties will include dispensing of clinical trial medication, stock management and maintenance of clinical trial records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to be flexible depending on the needs of the service and work some weekends and Bank Holidays on a rotational basis (at the Bristol Royal Infirmary pharmacy).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Liz McCullagh, Lead Clinical trials pharmacist - pharmacytrials@uhbw.nhs.uk, 0117 3424175&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gemma Paris Senior Clinical trials Pharmacy technician gemma.paris@uhbw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
